The National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), the country's top political advisory body, held a press conference on Friday afternoon ahead of the opening of its annual session. Guo Weimin, spokesperson for the first session of the 14th CPPCC National Committee, briefed the media on the session and took questions from reporters. The CPPCC will open its session on March 4 and conclude on March 11, Guo said.